9 318     Alas, I blame you not, for you are mortal,
9 319     And mortal eyes cannot endure the devil.
9 320     Avaunt, thou dreadful minister of hell!
9 321     Thou hadst but power over his mortal body,
9 322     His soul thou canst not have; therefore, be gone.
9 323   GLOUCESTER. Sweet saint, for charity, be not so curst.
9 324   ANNE. Foul devil, for God's sake, hence and trouble us not;
