9 587                      Enter BUCKINGHAM and DERBY
9 588 
9 589   GREY. Here come the Lords of Buckingham and Derby.
9 590   BUCKINGHAM. Good time of day unto your royal Grace!
9 591   DERBY. God make your Majesty joyful as you have been.
9 592   QUEEN ELIZABETH. The Countess Richmond, good my Lord
9 593     of Derby,
9 594     To your good prayer will scarcely say amen.
9 595     Yet, Derby, notwithstanding she's your wife
9 596     And loves not me, be you, good lord, assur'd
